## Self-Review

- Spec coverage: The plan covers the workbench shell, project list, task queue summary, current task execution, workflow steps, Agent Run timeline, manual gate actions, engineering feedback, settings center, Agent Profile configuration, Workflow Template configuration, Capability Packs, and Runner Logs.
- Deferred scope: Team permissions, real remote collaboration, automatic RAG ranking, and real cloud Agent scheduling remain out of the first implementation, matching the design spec.
- Risk: The first version uses fixtures and local UI state. Real runner integration needs a later plan that defines process lifecycle, worktree permissions, log streaming, and approval boundaries.
- Verification: Each implementation task has either a test command, build command, or browser check, and the final task requires desktop and mobile visual verification.
